@node "Einführung" "Etiketti 2.60 - Introduction"

 @{u}Introduction@{uu}

 Etiketti is a program to create labes for 3 1/2
 inch disks. With Etiketti you can read the directory
 from the disk, edit it, add a comment and print the
 labels on a DIN A4 paper sheet.
@endnode

@node "Systemvoraussetzungen" "Etiketti 2.60 - System requirements"

 @{u}System requirements@{uu}

 Etiketti should work on any Amiga with Amiga OS 2.0 or
 higher.

 To print the labels you need a graphics printer. Etiketti
 was tested with the Epson Stylus Color printer.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Etiketti 2.60 - Installation"

 @{u}Installation@{uu}

 At the moment it exists no installation program for Etiketti, so
 you must install it manually. To install Etiketti copy the drawer
 with the program to a place on your hard disk. After you have
 copied Etiketti you can start it as every other program to.

 The built in language in Etiketti is german. When you need the
 english translation, you must copy the Etiketti.catalog file to
 SYS:Locale/Catalogs/English. You can find this file in the Archive
 in the drawer Etiketti/Catalogs/English. For the english translation
 you need Amiga OS 2.1 or higher.
@endnode

@node "Bedienung" "Etiketti 2.60 - Operating instructions"

 @{u}Operating instructions@{uu}

 The @{"GUI" alink "EtikettiGUI.ilbm/main" 0} of Etiketti is structured in five groups. The function
 of this five groups is explained below. The functions of
 this five groups are explained from left to right and from
 top to bottom.


 @{u}Group drives@{uu}

 @{fg highlight}DF0:@{fg text}
 Reads the directory from drive DF0.

 @{fg highlight}PC0:@{fg text}
 Reads the directory from drive PC0.

 @{fg highlight}Other disk@{fg text}
 Cancel editing of current disk.


 @{u}Group files@{uu}

 @{fg highlight}Next name@{fg text}
 Goes to the next name of the directory without
 print this name to the label.

 @{fg highlight}Accept name@{fg text}
 Prints this name on the actual label.

 @{fg highlight}View gadget@{fg text}
 Show the actual disk or file name with its original
 length.

 @{fg highlight}Next dir@{fg text}
 Goes to the next subdirectory of the disk.

 @{fg highlight}Accept changed@{fg text}
 Prints the changed name from the edit gadget on the
 label.

 @{fg highlight}Edit gadget@{fg text}
 Shows the disk or file name in the length it will print
 on the label. In this gadget you also can edit this
 name. This don't affect the real name on the disk.


 @{u}Group commen@{uu}t

 @{fg highlight}Accept actual comment@{fg text}
 Prints the comment from the comment cycle gadget to
 the label. Is in the comment cycle gadget is
 "Own comment" choosen it will prints the text from
 the comment edit gadget on the label.

 @{fg highlight}Comment cycle gadget@{fg text}
 Gadget with some predefined comments.

 @{fg highlight}Comment edit gadget@{fg text}
 Gadget to enter your own comment.


 @{u}Group printer@{uu}

 @{fg highlight}Label position field@{fg text}
 The 12 buttons of this field shows on which position
 on the DIN A4 paper sheet labels will be print. Positions
 on which a label will be print are marked with a crook.

 @{fg highlight}Clear label@{fg text}
 After choosing this button you can remove a label from the
 label position field.

 @{fg highlight}Accept label@{fg text}
 Put the actual edited label to the label position field.
 After choosing this label you must chose a position on the
 label position field for the new label.

 @{fg highlight}Print@{fg text}
 Prints the DIN A4 paper sheet with the labels.

 @{fg highlight}Configuration@{fg text}
 By choosing this button the Window for the
 @{"printer configuration" link "Einstellungen" 0} appears.


 @{u}Group actual label@{uu}

 Shows the actual edited label.
@endnode

@node "Fehler" "Etiketti 2.60 - Known bugs"

 @{u}Known bugs@{uu}

 In the moment Etiketti don't work with Turbospool. I don't know
 if this is a problem from Etiketti or Turbospool. When you will
 use Etiketti, please deactivate Turbospool.
@endnode

@node "Aenderungen" "Etiketti 2.60 - History"

 @{u}History@{uu}

 @{b}2.50 -> 2.60@{ub}

 Maximum vertical offset increased to 220.0

 Error in printing routine solved. Etiketti crashes for some
 printer resolutions and vertical offsets.
@endnode

@node "Zukunft" "Etiketti 2.60 - Future"

 @{u}Future@{uu}

 Eventual I will make some enhancements to Etiketti in the
 future. I zhink about the following enhancements:

 - Less memory consumption for the printer routine.

 - A better comment system.

 - MUI graphical user interface.

 - Installer Script.

 The current version of Etiketti is good enough for my personnal
 use, so I only will develop the program if other persons also
 use Etiketti. When you use Etiketti and you are interested for
 better versions, please write me a letter, a postcard or a EMail.
 You can find my address in the chapter @{"author" link "Autor" 0}.
@endnode

